observations.recommendation:
We recommended the City Mayor to instruct the:

(a) CSWD Officer to (i) ensure that profiling of beneficiaries of future assistance is meticulously done to preclude erroneous payments; 

(ii) seek the DSWD’s approval prior to making payment to beneficiaries not included in their originally-approved list; 

(iii) refrain from keeping in her custody any refunds of cash assistance and advise said payees to make their refunds direct to the City Treasurer’s Office (CTO); 

(iv) ensure that complete eligibility documents are submitted before cash pay-outs are made; and 

(v) observe the timely submission of required reports; 

(b) City Treasurer to inform the CSWDO of any refunds of similar benefits as basis in requesting for authority in the subsequent use of the cash returned; 

(c) heads of City Offices concerned to (i) continue in effectively managing and utilizing government funds and resources during the COVID-19 pandemic and beyond as called for in R.A. No. 11469 and Section 2 of P.D. No. 1445 and other pertinent rules and regulations; and 

(ii) ensure that governments funds are safeguarded against loss or wastage.

We recommended the City Mayor to instruct the:

(a) City Accountant to (i) report and disclose in the quarterly and year-end financial statements the status of donations-in-kind received;

(ii) request the CGSO for the submission of MRSMI that shall serve as basis in recording the issuance of inventories; 


(b) City Health Officer to (i) report to the CGSO any inventories officially received from DOH or any source; 


(ii) ensure that items for personal use are removed from the CHO stockroom; 


(iii) maintain adequate records of supplies inventories kept at the CHO; 


(c) CGS Officer to report to the City Accountant (i) receipts of inventoriable materials; and 

(ii) issuances of stocks through the MRSMI; and 


(d) City Accountant, CGS Officer and City Health Officer to coordinate for the proper accounting of its inventories, in accordance with applicable rules and regulations and best practices in inventory management.
